BinaryTree

Class GeneralProcedures

  • java.lang.Object
    • BinaryTree.GeneralProcedures

  • public class GeneralProcedures
extends java.lang.Object
    Last edited 1/5/2022
    A collection of static procedures commonly used on general binary trees. These are separate from the search tree procedures for clarity.
    The syntax before each method is to allow for generic typing. This allows the methods to run on nodes that use any kind of comparable object.

      • toString

        public static <T> java.lang.String toString(Node<T> root,
                                            int numLevels)
        Creates a string visual representation of a node. Note that the size of the string will grow exponentially with the height of the node, so this works best for smallish balanced trees. Also spacing works best for monospace fonts.
        Type Parameters:
        T - node key type
        Parameters:
        root - root node
        numLevels - number of levels to print
        Returns:
